  <description><![CDATA[<p>The lovely Hotel Pic Blanc is located in the Bergers area of <a data-udi="umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497" href="/{localLink:umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497}" title="Alpe d'Huez">Alpe d'Huez</a>. Tastefully decorated inside and out, the hotel blends well into the environment and has awe-inspiring views across the valley.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring Alpe d'Huez, there's nowhere better to be than soaking in a pool or sauna. The hotel has good wellness facilities, which you can book and pay for locally. The facilities include an indoor swimming pool, sauna and hammam, for those looking to relax after a day enjoying the varied and extensive skiing. Alternatively, there's a warm and welcoming lounge and bar area with a open fire, so you can cosy up for an evening in.</p>
<h2>Good location</h2>
<p>Located in the Les Bergers area of the resort, you are just a short walk away from the ski lifts, the ski school meeting point and beginner's ski area are also opposite the hotel. <a data-udi="umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497" href="/{localLink:umb://document/acff50eb9ad84862a464f68b551bc497}" title="Alpe d'Huez">Alpe d'Huez</a> has 250km of slopes, with its choice of varied runs in the sun, it is well suited to all levels of skier and boarders - and the perfect location for a family holiday.</p>]]></description>
