  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Superior Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 21m². These rooms are also available for sole occupancy.</p>
<p><strong>Privilege Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 27m². These rooms are also available for sole occupancy. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Family Rooms</strong> sleep two to four people and are around 27m². These rooms have a sofa bed which is suitable for two children up to 11 years or one adult and have a balcony with village views.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Family Rooms with Mountain Views</strong> sleep two to four people and are around 27m². These rooms have a sofa bed which is suitable for two children up to 11 years or 1 adult and a balcony with views of the mountains and/ or the <span>Sarenne valley</span>.</p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Twin or double beds (please specify when booking)</li>
<li>A bath with a showerhead attachment or shower room</li>
<li>Most rooms have a balcony with resort or slope views (supplements may apply)</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>TV with some English speaking channels </li>
<li>Tea and coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Desk</li>
<li>Telephone</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>Towels </li>
<li>Bed linen</li>
<li>Daily house keeping</li>
<li>Baby cots are available on request (free) for children under 2 years old.</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
